  "prompt": "How do you know that the girl sitting next to you wants you to talk to her?",
  "response": "There are several nonverbal cues and social signals that can indicate someone is open to conversation. Here are a few signs to look for:\n\n1. **Eye Contact**: If she frequently looks your way and maintains eye contact, it can suggest she\u2019s interested in interacting.\n\n2. **Body Language**: Open and relaxed body language, such as facing you, leaning slightly in your direction, or uncrossed arms, typically indicates she is welcoming conversation.\n\n3. **Smiling**: A genuine smile can be a strong sign that she is friendly and approachable.\n\n4. **Proximity**: If she\u2019s sitting close to you rather than distant, it can indicate an openness to engage in conversation.\n\n5. **Initiating Actions**: If she has made any small gestures towards conversation, like glancing at you or trying to engage in a group discussion you are part of, it may show interest.\n\n6. **Responding to Your Presence**: If she reacts positively when you speak or shows awareness of you being there, she might be interested in talking.\n\nIf you notice some of these signals, it\u2019s generally a good sign that she may want to chat. Remember to approach the conversation respectfully and be aware of her responses as you engage.",
